description: Manage application types on an Azure Service Fabric cluster.

commands.name: az sf application-type create
commands.summary: Create a new application type on an Azure Service Fabric cluster.
examples: az sf application-type create -g testRG -c testCluster --application-type-name testAppType

commands.name: az sf application-type delete
examples: az sf application-type delete -g testRG -c testCluster --application-type-name CalcServiceApp

commands.name: az sf application-type list
commands.summary: List application types of a given cluster.
examples: az sf application-type list -g testRG -c testCluster

commands.name: az sf application-type show
commands.summary: Show the properties of an application type on an Azure Service Fabric cluster.
examples: az sf application-type show -g testRG -c testCluster --application-type-name CalcServiceApp
